"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-05-paris-2024-olympics-dtigress-to-face-usa-in-quarter-final\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's D'Tigress will square up with holders, United States of America in the quarter-finals at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games.  Rena Wakama's side sealed their place in the last-eight after a hard-earned 79-70 victory over Canada on Sunday.  The African champions finished the group stage with two wins and one defeat.  D'Tigress defeated Australia 75-62 in their opening fixture but lost to host nation France 75-54 in the second game.  They made history as the first African basketball team (male or female) to reach the quarter-finals at the Olympics.  USA on the other hand won all three group games against Japan, Belgium and Germany.  The encounter will hold at the Stade Pierre-Mauroy Arena, Lille on Wednesday.  Transfer: Tanzanian club, Simba SC unveil Okejepha  Ronaldo vs Messi: I have never seen any player like him - Quique Flores picks GOAT  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  Why I dropped Cristiano Ronaldo from Portugal squad to play USA, Mexico - Martinez  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  2026 FIBA World Cup Qualifiers: D'Tigress rally to 101-84 victory over Philippines  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"